  <script>
    // Function to update the Building options based on the selected Campus
    function updateBuildingOptions() {
      const campusSelect = document.getElementById('box1');
      const buildingSelect = document.getElementById('box3');
      const areaSelect = document.getElementById('box5');

      // Clear existing options in both building and area dropdowns
      buildingSelect.innerHTML = '<option value="">Select a Building</option>';
      areaSelect.innerHTML = '<option value="">Select an Area</option>';

      // Define building options for both campuses
      const buildingOptions = {
        'Coral Gables': ['Ashe Administration', 'Allen Hall'],
        'Rosenstiel Campus': ['CIMAS', 'SLAB']
      };

      // Get the selected campus
      const selectedCampus = campusSelect.value;

      // Populate the building dropdown based on the selected campus
      if (selectedCampus) {
        buildingOptions[selectedCampus].forEach(building => {
          const option = document.createElement('option');
          option.textContent = building;
          option.value = building;
          buildingSelect.appendChild(option);
        });
      }

      // Trigger the update for the "Area #" dropdown when the campus changes
      updateAreaOptions();
    }

    // Function to update the Area options based on the selected Building
    function updateAreaOptions() {
      const buildingSelect = document.getElementById('box3');
      const areaSelect = document.getElementById('box5');

      // Clear existing options in the area dropdown
      areaSelect.innerHTML = '<option value="">Select an Area</option>';

      // Get the selected building
      const selectedBuilding = buildingSelect.value;

      // If a building is selected, populate the area dropdown with common areas
      if (selectedBuilding) {
        const commonAreas = ['100', '101', '101A', '101B'];
        commonAreas.forEach(area => {
          const option = document.createElement('option');
          option.textContent = area;
          option.value = area;
          areaSelect.appendChild(option);
        });
      }
    }


    // Function to read URL parameters and set input field values
    function setValuesFromURLParams() {
      const urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
      const campus = urlParams.get('campus');
      const building = urlParams.get('building');
      const area = urlParams.get('area');
      const requestorName = urlParams.get('requestorName');
      const requestorEmail = urlParams.get('requestorEmail');
      const actionRequested = urlParams.get('actionRequested');

      // Set input field values based on the URL parameters
      if (campus) {
        document.getElementById('box1').value = campus;
        // Trigger the update for the "Building Name" dropdown
        updateBuildingOptions();
      }
      if (building) {
        document.getElementById('box3').value = building;
        // Trigger the update for the "Area #" dropdown
        updateAreaOptions();
      }
      if (area) document.getElementById('box5').value = area;
      if (requestorName) document.getElementById('box2').value = requestorName;
      if (requestorEmail) document.getElementById('box4').value = requestorEmail;
      if (actionRequested) document.getElementById('box6').value = actionRequested;
    }

    // Call the function to set input field values on page load
    setValuesFromURLParams();
  </script>
